(3)

Here, the hyperparameter $\sigma_t \in [0, \min\{1, \frac{1-\alpha_{t-1}}{\alpha_t}\}]$ controls the re-masking probability for already unmasked tokens. A key practical challenge of this method is that $\sigma_t$ is determined by one of several proposed schedules, each governed by a hyperparameter $\eta$ that must be carefully tuned (see Appendix C.1). While this enables error correction that is compatible with pre-trained models, its effectiveness is limited by the non-selective nature of the remasking schedule, motivating a more targeted approach.
